All phases complete. Here's the summary:

## Bead noscope-bsq.1.1: Complete

**What was implemented:**

- **`ConfigPathError`** тАФ typed error struct with `name()` and `reason()` accessors, `Display`, `Debug`, `std::error::Error`, `Send + Sync`
- **`validate_config_name()`** тАФ strict allowlist validation (ASCII alphanumeric, `-`, `_`, `.`; rejects empty, `.`, `..`, everything else)
- **`named_config_toml_path()`** тАФ changed from `-> PathBuf` to `-> Result<PathBuf, ConfigPathError>`
- Updated all callers: `provider_config_path`, `profile_config_path`, `Client::resolve_provider`, `resolve_provider_config`
- **`From<ConfigPathError> for Error`** тАФ maps to `ErrorKind::Security` (exit code 64)

**Test coverage: 38 tests** covering:
- Path separator rejection (`/`, `\`, `../../etc/passwd`, Windows-style traversal)
- Dot traversal rejection (`.`, `..`)
- Primitive rejection (empty, NUL, control chars, whitespace, colon, tilde, non-ASCII unicode)
- Valid name acceptance (alphanumeric, hyphens, underscores, dots, dotfiles, mixed case)
- Typed error properties (name, reason, Display, `std::error::Error`, `Send + Sync`)
- End-to-end provider/profile paths (XDG, HOME resolution)
- Error kind mapping (`ConfigPathError` тЖТ `ErrorKind::Security`)

**Quality gates:** 787 tests pass, zero clippy warnings, `cargo fmt` clean.
